olive oil
1 tin sweetcorn
1 carrot
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 packet Ginger Paste
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
drizzle vinegar (white  wine or rice wine)
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 packet coriander

• Drain sweetcorn. Grate carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. When oil is hot, cook ginger paste, sweet soy seasoning and diced chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey. Toss to coat.

TIP: Chicken is cooked when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot, sweetcorn, mayonnaise and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.

• Divide slaw between bowls.
• Top with soy-ginger chicken, spooning over any remaining sauce from the pan.
• Sprinkle with crispy shallots and tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!